# Business & Product Leadership (Condensed)

## Business Strategy & Discovery
- **JTBD**: "When [Situation], I want to [Motivation], so I can [Outcome]"
- **Diffusion**: Innovators (2.5%) → Early Adopters (13.5%) → Chasm → Early Majority (34%)
- **MVP target**: Early Adopters first, beachhead strategy, cross Chasm later

## Product Metrics & Analytics
- **North Star Metric**: Single metric capturing core customer value (e.g., Airbnb = nights booked)
- **Metrics Hierarchy**: Business Outcome → Product Health (retention, engagement, activation) → Feature Performance
- **Cohort Analysis**: Track retention by sign-up week; flattening curve = PMF signal
- **Funnel Analysis**: Sign-up → Onboarding → First Value → Retention → Revenue; fix biggest drop-off first

## A/B Testing & Experimentation
- **Hypothesis**: "We believe [change] will [impact] because [reason]"
- **Sample size**: Calculate before running (statsmodels/power analysis)
- **Duration**: Min 1 full business cycle, typically 2 weeks
- **Don't peek early** — inflates false positive rate
- **Primary + secondary metrics**: Success metric + guardrails
- **Practical significance**: Is the lift worth the effort?

## Pricing & Monetization
- **Value-based pricing** (recommended): Price at 20-30% of value delivered
- **Freemium**: Free = core JTBD + usage limit; Pro = unlimited + advanced; Enterprise = custom
- **Unit economics**: LTV:CAC ratio 3:1-5:1 = healthy; Payback < 12 months = excellent

## User Research
- **Personas**: Demographics, goals, pains, behaviors, JTBD
- **Journey Map**: Awareness → Consideration → Onboarding → First Value → Regular Use → Advocacy
- **Usability Testing**: 5 users, think-aloud, measure success rate + time + errors + SUS

## Go-to-Market
- **Positioning**: For [X] who [Y], our product is a [Z] that [benefit], unlike [competitor]
- **Launch Playbook**: Pre-launch (4w: beta + case study + docs) → Launch (PH/HN + email + social) → Post-launch (feedback + fixes + case study)

## Product-Market Fit Measurement
- **Sean Ellis Test**: ≥ 40% "Very disappointed" if product gone = PMF
- **Retention Curve**: Flattening = PMF; declining to zero = no PMF
- **Superhuman Survey**: 4 questions → segment "Very disappointed" users by persona

## Ship != Release
- **Ship**: Code to prod behind feature flags (technical)
- **Release**: Turn on flags for users (business), phased via Rogers gates

## Integration
- `why-strategic-rationale` → WHY feeds JTBD
